WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:54.346 --> 00:00:57.498
SUMMER 2024. HO CHI MINH

3
00:01:01.802 --> 00:01:04.304
They say that Kathleen
has moved to Korea.

4
00:01:05.967 --> 00:01:07.718
Do you think the flight will take off?

5
00:01:08.511 --> 00:01:09.345
Kathleen?

6
00:01:09.956 --> 00:01:12.250
Yeah. it's the name
of this typhoon.

7
00:01:13.241 --> 00:01:15.149
Do you know why typhoons
have pretty names?

8
00:01:16.603 --> 00:01:17.395
Why?

9
00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:18.550
They say...

10
00:01:18.634 --> 00:01:20.704
...to make them pass by gently.

11
00:01:21.622 --> 00:01:24.583
But you know. it never happens.

12
00:01:35.931 --> 00:01:37.450
Hello.

13
00:01:37.591 --> 00:01:38.884
Hello. welcome.

14
00:01:39.407 --> 00:01:41.743
This way. please.

15
00:01:41.798 --> 00:01:42.757
Welcome aboard.

16
00:01:45.032 --> 00:01:45.921
Hello.

17
00:01:47.582 --> 00:01:50.731
This way. please.

18
00:01:52.678 --> 00:01:53.721
Welcome.

19
00:02:59.519 --> 00:03:04.066
ONCE WE WERE US

20
00:03:06.360 --> 00:03:07.658
<i>Beijing Olympics news.</i>

21
00:03:07.835 --> 00:03:10.447
<i>With the Beijing Olympics set to begin
on August 8th. athletes are...</i>

22
00:03:10.531 --> 00:03:11.740
SUMMER 2008. SEOUL

23
00:03:12.505 --> 00:03:17.993
<i>Heavy rain of between 200
and 480 millimeters has fallen.</i>

24
00:03:18.310 --> 00:03:20.023
<i>Due to this. floods and landslides...</i>

25
00:03:20.208 --> 00:03:22.001
<i>...caused at least 86 power outages...</i>

26
00:03:22.085 --> 00:03:24.337
<i>...and affected more than 140 homes.</i>

27
00:03:24.427 --> 00:03:27.096
<i>Beware of landslides
while traveling in vehicles...</i>

28
00:03:27.187 --> 00:03:28.590
<i>...or on foot near mountains.</i>

29
00:03:33.513 --> 00:03:36.183
ORIGINAL FILM <US AND THEM>
DIRECTED BY RENE LIU

30
00:04:17.852 --> 00:04:19.061
- Thank you.
- No problem.

31
00:04:32.582 --> 00:04:33.457
Excuse me.

32
00:04:48.570 --> 00:04:51.348
I think you're sitting in my seat.

33
00:04:53.298 --> 00:04:54.104
Pardon?

34
00:04:54.807 --> 00:04:56.982
No. 30 is my seat.

35
00:05:00.131 --> 00:05:02.454
Oh. mine is the aisle seat?

36
00:05:02.551 --> 00:05:03.023
Sorry.

37
00:05:03.049 --> 00:05:06.179
No. no. no! It's okay.
You can sit there.

38
00:05:08.807 --> 00:05:11.435
- No. 31 is my seat.
- Oh. I'm sorry.

39
00:05:20.668 --> 00:05:22.339
We'll be departing now.

40
00:05:22.485 --> 00:05:24.797
Please fasten your seatbelts.

41
00:06:41.398 --> 00:06:43.383
That was a close call.

42
00:06:44.396 --> 00:06:45.485
Are you okay?

43
00:06:49.066 --> 00:06:50.275
I'm fine.

44
00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:54.956
- Here.
- Thank you.

45
00:06:55.928 --> 00:06:57.021
Is this me?

46
00:06:57.286 --> 00:06:58.016
No.

47
00:06:58.050 --> 00:06:59.489
No. it's not you.

48
00:06:59.618 --> 00:07:00.678
Yes. it is.

49
00:07:06.404 --> 00:07:07.469
I'm sorry.

50
00:07:08.997 --> 00:07:10.744
It's okay. I'm flattered.

51
00:07:12.319 --> 00:07:14.531
Everyone. there's a landslide.

52
00:07:14.559 --> 00:07:15.885
I can't go any further.

53
00:07:16.831 --> 00:07:19.611
It'll take about 2 hours
to clean up and such.

54
00:07:19.889 --> 00:07:21.584
Please call someone to come and get you.

55
00:07:22.698 --> 00:07:24.074
What if there's no one to call?

56
00:07:24.186 --> 00:07:26.904
Then you'll have to wait here.

57
00:07:28.830 --> 00:07:30.999
<i>May I have your attention. please.</i>

58
00:07:31.089 --> 00:07:32.663
<i>Our flight has been canceled...</i>

59
00:07:32.690 --> 00:07:35.851
<i>...due to inclement weather in Incheon.</i>

60
00:07:36.852 --> 00:07:37.703
<i>We apologize for...</i>

61
00:07:37.729 --> 00:07:39.690
Please follow the instructions
off the plane...

62
00:07:39.736 --> 00:07:42.585
...and we will assist
with flight changes at the counter.

63
00:07:43.093 --> 00:07:44.567
This way. please.

64
00:08:01.712 --> 00:08:02.625
<i>Hey.</i>

65
00:08:04.752 --> 00:08:06.420
Could you step aside?

66
00:08:06.932 --> 00:08:07.766
Ah. okay.

67
00:08:12.396 --> 00:08:13.647
I'm done filming.

68
00:08:14.468 --> 00:08:15.507
Okay.

69
00:08:24.986 --> 00:08:27.141
Can you give me
that drawing from earlier?

70
00:08:29.227 --> 00:08:30.200
The drawing?

71
00:08:30.617 --> 00:08:32.828
Don't worry.
I got rid of it already.

72
00:08:33.245 --> 00:08:34.794
I actually wanted it...

73
00:08:35.776 --> 00:08:36.623
But alright.

74
00:08:39.126 --> 00:08:40.252
Hey.

75
00:08:50.359 --> 00:08:51.360
Hold on.

76
00:09:06.168 --> 00:09:07.235
Thanks.

77
00:09:07.468 --> 00:09:08.347
No worries.

78
00:09:15.964 --> 00:09:17.257
Lee Eun-ho!

79
00:09:20.453 --> 00:09:22.271
Dad. the mountain's collapsed!

80
00:09:22.332 --> 00:09:24.440
I knew this would happen someday.

81
00:09:24.855 --> 00:09:25.522
Get in. quickly!

82
00:09:25.616 --> 00:09:27.302
Good grief. What happened?

83
00:09:38.834 --> 00:09:39.804
Hold on.

84
00:09:45.487 --> 00:09:46.443
Hey.

85
00:09:49.352 --> 00:09:50.071
Yes?

86
00:09:52.224 --> 00:09:53.165
Uh...

87
00:09:53.311 --> 00:09:56.726
Please. calm down.
Everybody. please calm down.

88
00:09:56.791 --> 00:09:58.960
We're so sorry.
Please get in line.

89
00:09:59.533 --> 00:10:00.554
There's no room available.

90
00:10:00.580 --> 00:10:01.138
Sorry.

91
00:10:01.164 --> 00:10:03.627
- Okey? You should try the next hotel...
- Is there any room left?

92
00:10:03.970 --> 00:10:05.171
We're sorry.

93
00:10:05.458 --> 00:10:07.322
This gentleman took the last room.

94
00:10:22.963 --> 00:10:23.797
Come in.

95
00:10:24.625 --> 00:10:25.540
Okay.

96
00:11:03.819 --> 00:11:05.192
Looks like Kathleen...

97
00:11:05.290 --> 00:11:07.146
...passed through here smoothly.

98
00:11:08.310 --> 00:11:10.385
but things don't look good for Korea.

99
00:11:11.328 --> 00:11:15.001
I heard it's the strongest
typhoon in 80 years.

100
00:11:15.916 --> 00:11:17.834
The night market must be ruined.

101
00:11:18.508 --> 00:11:19.506
Night market?

102
00:11:20.494 --> 00:11:25.191
There's a night market
across from the hotel here.

103
00:11:25.463 --> 00:11:26.594
Been there?

104
00:11:26.729 --> 00:11:27.820
Yes...

105
00:11:28.196 --> 00:11:30.664
...and to the river and
the temple on the other side.

106
00:11:32.971 --> 00:11:34.480
There was a temple too?

107
00:11:37.243 --> 00:11:38.679
Really...

108
00:11:49.019 --> 00:11:50.080
It's good to see you.

109
00:11:54.123 --> 00:11:54.932
Me too.

110
00:11:56.709 --> 00:11:57.710
It's been a long time.

111
00:12:17.403 --> 00:12:19.152
You want to get off
at the bus terminal?

112
00:12:19.795 --> 00:12:21.739
Yes. sir. Thank you.

113
00:12:23.396 --> 00:12:25.374
Is this your hometown. Jeong-won?

114
00:12:26.402 --> 00:12:28.842
I wasn't born here. but I grew up here.

115
00:12:29.222 --> 00:12:31.266
It's your hometown. then.

116
00:12:32.758 --> 00:12:35.803
You both started college in '06?

117
00:12:35.857 --> 00:12:37.597
Eun-ho. she's the same age.

118
00:12:37.646 --> 00:12:38.879
Dad. I went to college
2 years late.

119
00:12:38.941 --> 00:12:40.274
Let's just go quietly.

120
00:12:40.604 --> 00:12:41.974
Jeong-won. aren't you hungry?

121
00:12:42.312 --> 00:12:43.726
I'm okay. sir.

122
00:12:44.046 --> 00:12:45.478
Eat before you go.

123
00:12:45.652 --> 00:12:47.209
I run a restaurant.

124
00:12:47.463 --> 00:12:50.323
I don't mean to brag.
but it's famous here.

125
00:12:50.746 --> 00:12:52.289
Dad. just go to the terminal.

126
00:12:52.402 --> 00:12:54.313
Should I stop babbling?

127
00:12:54.356 --> 00:12:55.016
Please.

128
00:12:55.179 --> 00:12:56.897
One bite...

129
00:12:56.930 --> 00:12:59.561
...and you'll know
this is the local favorite!

130
00:13:01.276 --> 00:13:02.483
She's busy.

131
00:13:02.509 --> 00:13:03.475
No. I'm not.

132
00:13:03.573 --> 00:13:04.644
What's your main dish?

133
00:13:05.060 --> 00:13:06.699
Spicy seafood noodles!

134
00:13:07.062 --> 00:13:07.917
Wow!

135
00:13:08.144 --> 00:13:10.188
This is on the house.

136
00:13:10.806 --> 00:13:11.698
Wow!

137
00:13:11.877 --> 00:13:13.180
I cut them up real good.

138
00:13:13.727 --> 00:13:15.349
- Thank you. sir!
- Sure.

139
00:13:17.293 --> 00:13:18.420
What are you doing?

140
00:13:18.446 --> 00:13:19.914
Come here and eat.

141
00:13:25.568 --> 00:13:26.532
How is it?

142
00:13:26.927 --> 00:13:28.220
It's delicious!

143
00:13:28.321 --> 00:13:29.695
Do you want to take some home?

144
00:13:29.861 --> 00:13:31.092
No. it's okay. sir.

145
00:13:32.768 --> 00:13:34.197
Eat up.

146
00:13:38.248 --> 00:13:40.099
Eun-ho. when should
we go see your mom?

147
00:13:40.362 --> 00:13:41.725
Let's go tomorrow morning.

148
00:13:42.340 --> 00:13:43.588
Think it'll rain again?

149
00:13:44.254 --> 00:13:46.313
The urn's inside. It'll be okay.

150
00:13:46.382 --> 00:13:49.077
I meant your mom loved the rain.

151
00:13:50.293 --> 00:13:51.547
She's beautiful.

152
00:13:51.822 --> 00:13:53.055
I look like my mom.

153
00:13:53.423 --> 00:13:55.224
You look like me!

154
00:13:55.690 --> 00:13:56.892
Please don't say that.

155
00:13:56.926 --> 00:13:58.450
- What are you here for?
- To do the dishes.

156
00:13:58.503 --> 00:13:59.730
Stay out.

157
00:14:00.297 --> 00:14:03.650
Leave it. Wipe the table instead.

158
00:14:09.466 --> 00:14:10.818
Did you draw all this?

159
00:14:11.239 --> 00:14:12.966
I drew some of them...

160
00:14:13.552 --> 00:14:15.339
...and mom drew the rest.

161
00:14:15.952 --> 00:14:17.104
Our styles are similar.

162
00:14:17.731 --> 00:14:19.024
You're an art major?

163
00:14:19.456 --> 00:14:20.831
No. computer engineering.

164
00:14:21.506 --> 00:14:22.234
What?

165
00:14:22.353 --> 00:14:23.124
Jeez.

166
00:14:24.287 --> 00:14:25.932
Eun-ho. Can you open this?

167
00:14:26.574 --> 00:14:28.152
- Ow. my wrist.
- Can't even open this?

168
00:14:30.863 --> 00:14:31.885
What the heck?

169
00:14:34.791 --> 00:14:35.604
Let me try.

170
00:14:41.131 --> 00:14:42.132
Wow!

171
00:14:42.786 --> 00:14:44.291
I should've packed you some food.

172
00:14:44.373 --> 00:14:45.942
No. it's okay. really.

173
00:14:46.070 --> 00:14:47.388
Come back anytime.

174
00:14:47.471 --> 00:14:48.663
Thank you. sir.

175
00:14:48.945 --> 00:14:49.970
Be careful riding.

176
00:14:51.135 --> 00:14:52.410
Drop her off safely.

177
00:14:53.853 --> 00:14:58.208
EUN-HO'S DINER

178
00:15:18.920 --> 00:15:20.815
- Thanks. Take care.
- Bye.

179
00:15:25.657 --> 00:15:27.232
EVERGREEN ORPHANAGE

180
00:15:30.697 --> 00:15:31.570
Aren't you going?

181
00:15:31.792 --> 00:15:32.808
Right. Bye.

182
00:15:57.350 --> 00:15:58.643
Hello.

183
00:16:00.798 --> 00:16:01.925
May I help you?

184
00:16:02.245 --> 00:16:04.576
Is the director here?

185
00:16:05.066 --> 00:16:07.142
She went home for vacation.

186
00:16:08.449 --> 00:16:09.258
Home?

187
00:16:09.485 --> 00:16:10.701
Yes. her home.

188
00:16:10.733 --> 00:16:13.926
This isn't her real house. you know.

189
00:16:15.119 --> 00:16:16.099
By chance.

190
00:16:16.370 --> 00:16:18.524
are you from here?

191
00:16:21.285 --> 00:16:24.955
Then come in.
The other caretakers are here.

192
00:16:27.175 --> 00:16:28.459
No. it's okay.

193
00:16:29.245 --> 00:16:30.913
Please give this to the kids.

194
00:16:31.407 --> 00:16:33.474
You shouldn't have.

195
00:16:33.544 --> 00:16:36.256
Thank you!

196
00:17:16.281 --> 00:17:17.281
All done here?

197
00:17:18.227 --> 00:17:19.186
Yeah.

198
00:17:21.020 --> 00:17:23.065
I wonder when the sun will go down.

199
00:17:31.199 --> 00:17:32.676
Let me drive. Get in the back.

200
00:17:33.249 --> 00:17:33.983
What?

201
00:17:37.226 --> 00:17:38.258
Do you know how to ride?

202
00:17:38.453 --> 00:17:39.384
Yeah.

203
00:17:43.968 --> 00:17:44.841
Grab on.

204
00:17:49.329 --> 00:17:50.083
Tight!

205
00:18:16.420 --> 00:18:19.204
What does it feel like
to go back home?

206
00:18:22.954 --> 00:18:24.633
Feels like... getting tired
of spicy seafood noodles?

207
00:18:27.606 --> 00:18:29.858
I want to build my own house.

208
00:18:30.441 --> 00:18:31.244
A house?

209
00:18:32.179 --> 00:18:33.650
Oh. really?

210
00:18:35.544 --> 00:18:36.965
I want to make a game.

211
00:18:37.512 --> 00:18:39.097
What? A game?

212
00:18:39.611 --> 00:18:40.483
Yes.

213
00:18:40.667 --> 00:18:42.680
Games can have multiple endings.

214
00:18:43.712 --> 00:18:46.809
I want to have
all kinds of fun endings.

215
00:18:46.923 --> 00:18:48.831
That's why you're studying
computer engineering?

216
00:18:49.163 --> 00:18:49.966
Yeah.

217
00:18:50.890 --> 00:18:52.223
Why are you majoring in social welfare...

218
00:18:52.270 --> 00:18:53.626
...instead of architecture?

219
00:18:54.341 --> 00:18:56.468
Because it got me a scholarship.

220
00:18:57.039 --> 00:18:58.974
I have no choice.

221
00:19:02.530 --> 00:19:04.007
What are you doing?

222
00:19:04.452 --> 00:19:05.682
Making a wish.

223
00:19:05.807 --> 00:19:06.628
A wish?

224
00:19:06.883 --> 00:19:10.047
From when the sun touches
the sea to when it disappears.

225
00:19:10.073 --> 00:19:12.453
say your wish 100 times
and it'll come true.

226
00:19:12.701 --> 00:19:13.955
You believe that?

227
00:19:14.101 --> 00:19:15.255
It's true.

228
00:19:16.830 --> 00:19:20.000
It works.
I got into college. didn't I?

229
00:19:20.821 --> 00:19:22.760
What am I. a sacrifice offering?

230
00:19:23.559 --> 00:19:24.741
You didn't know?

231
00:19:30.129 --> 00:19:30.977
It's time!

232
00:20:10.623 --> 00:20:12.542
Jsonsoft?

233
00:20:14.369 --> 00:20:15.735
You work at a nice company.

234
00:20:17.221 --> 00:20:18.163
You being here...

235
00:20:18.871 --> 00:20:20.067
...doesn't feel real.

236
00:20:20.919 --> 00:20:24.245
Almost like you're CG.

237
00:20:25.730 --> 00:20:26.866
Yeah.

238
00:20:28.638 --> 00:20:30.133
It brings back old memories.

239
00:20:32.201 --> 00:20:33.074
Right.

240
00:20:36.797 --> 00:20:38.270
Still searching?

241
00:20:39.647 --> 00:20:41.690
I told you.
you won't find it today.

242
00:20:41.892 --> 00:20:43.164
CYWORLD SEARCHING: HAN JEONG-WON

243
00:20:43.219 --> 00:20:47.301
Give it up and join the game.

244
00:20:47.530 --> 00:20:48.704
Let's start without him.

245
00:20:49.539 --> 00:20:51.047
- One on one?
- Sure.

246
00:20:53.432 --> 00:20:54.248
Burgers?

247
00:20:54.356 --> 00:20:55.854
- Winner buys.
- Okay!

248
00:20:56.414 --> 00:20:57.210
Ready!

249
00:20:58.570 --> 00:20:59.435
Strike one.

250
00:21:02.532 --> 00:21:05.343
TITLE: LOVE IS LIKE SPRING RAIN...

251
00:21:06.410 --> 00:21:07.411
Strike one.

252
00:21:07.579 --> 00:21:09.289
- Strike two.
- Wait! No!

253
00:21:09.373 --> 00:21:11.706
ANPOONG GAS STATION

254
00:21:12.960 --> 00:21:14.336
- Ready.
- Hold on.

255
00:21:14.420 --> 00:21:16.005
- Start!
- Seung-chan.

256
00:21:16.081 --> 00:21:16.946
Do it again!

257
00:21:16.980 --> 00:21:18.036
- Want me to buy gas?
- What?

258
00:21:18.278 --> 00:21:19.238
- Gas.
- What gas?

259
00:21:19.301 --> 00:21:19.996
I'll buy.

260
00:21:20.052 --> 00:21:20.775
What gas?

261
00:21:20.801 --> 00:21:21.824
- Hold on.
- Kyung-seok.

262
00:21:21.908 --> 00:21:23.445
Which is better? On or off?

263
00:21:23.471 --> 00:21:24.070
Off.

264
00:21:25.085 --> 00:21:27.081
- Is that her?
- Act like it's a coincidence.

265
00:21:27.171 --> 00:21:27.865
Act natural.

266
00:21:27.929 --> 00:21:30.229
- Calm down.
- Don't worry.

267
00:21:30.964 --> 00:21:32.299
How much would you like?

268
00:21:33.148 --> 00:21:34.228
$5. please.

269
00:21:35.095 --> 00:21:36.071
$5?

270
00:21:37.645 --> 00:21:38.372
Hey!

271
00:21:39.467 --> 00:21:40.464
Wish girl!

272
00:21:45.888 --> 00:21:46.722
Spicy noodles!

273
00:21:46.748 --> 00:21:48.706
- You work here?
- Spicy noodles?

274
00:21:48.740 --> 00:21:50.033
Why'd you come?

275
00:21:50.346 --> 00:21:51.880
I came to get gas.

276
00:21:56.311 --> 00:21:58.188
<i>Seoul is tough for everyone.</i>

277
00:21:59.541 --> 00:22:02.230
<i>For people who weren't born here.</i>

278
00:22:02.460 --> 00:22:04.009
<i>it's 10 times harder.</i>

279
00:22:05.315 --> 00:22:06.818
<i>After years of wandering.</i>

280
00:22:07.120 --> 00:22:08.884
<i>- I want to settle down somewhere.</i>
- Thank you.

281
00:22:10.270 --> 00:22:11.207
Soju. please.

282
00:22:11.234 --> 00:22:14.758
<i>Seoul is too hard and cold
like a concrete floor...</i>

283
00:22:16.540 --> 00:22:18.762
<i>...for me to get in and take root.</i>

284
00:22:20.544 --> 00:22:21.781
<i>Still.</i>

285
00:22:22.384 --> 00:22:24.497
<i>I'll have my own place someday.</i>

286
00:22:24.869 --> 00:22:28.122
MAKE 10 MILLION WITH A GAME

287
00:22:28.956 --> 00:22:31.584
NATIONAL UNIV. GAME CONTEST

288
00:22:33.475 --> 00:22:34.524
Hey. wish girl!

289
00:22:36.005 --> 00:22:37.778
- I'm Oh Kyung-seok.
- Hi.

290
00:22:39.001 --> 00:22:41.114
Game start! Game start!

291
00:22:41.720 --> 00:22:42.929
Numbers four and five!

292
00:22:43.199 --> 00:22:44.979
- One!
- Oops!

293
00:22:45.528 --> 00:22:48.261
- Wait. Is it this way?
- That's right.

294
00:22:54.191 --> 00:22:56.026
JEONG-WON

295
00:23:01.372 --> 00:23:02.633
Here. sir.

296
00:23:06.839 --> 00:23:07.997
All done. sir.

297
00:23:12.918 --> 00:23:17.163
I want to get into a big company!

298
00:23:17.314 --> 00:23:19.930
Silicon Valley. wait for me!

299
00:23:19.960 --> 00:23:23.137
I want to live in America!

300
00:23:23.821 --> 00:23:26.349
My own house in Seoul!

301
00:23:26.375 --> 00:23:28.902
- What? That's it?
- What a small dream!

302
00:23:28.928 --> 00:23:30.594
No way! That's not small!

303
00:23:30.620 --> 00:23:31.913
- It's not!
- It's not!

304
00:23:31.994 --> 00:23:34.839
Make $10 million with my game!

305
00:23:34.865 --> 00:23:37.099
- Make 10 million?
- Are you sure?

306
00:23:37.145 --> 00:23:40.016
- I can make $10 million!
- Do it!

307
00:23:43.270 --> 00:23:44.167
Come on!

308
00:23:44.201 --> 00:23:45.278
It's raining!

309
00:23:45.863 --> 00:23:50.326
- It's raining! Let's go!
- Hurry!

310
00:24:04.980 --> 00:24:06.249
Let's go!

311
00:24:06.575 --> 00:24:07.535
Where are you going?

312
00:24:07.643 --> 00:24:08.519
Somewhere nice.

313
00:24:08.616 --> 00:24:10.076
- Where?
- Seum.

314
00:24:10.620 --> 00:24:11.663
What's that?

315
00:24:11.908 --> 00:24:14.234
It's an architecture club.

316
00:24:14.374 --> 00:24:17.073
A senior member is buying drinks
to celebrate getting a job.

317
00:24:17.660 --> 00:24:18.921
Which senior?

318
00:24:19.002 --> 00:24:20.229
Like you'd know.

319
00:24:20.333 --> 00:24:21.243
Do you want to come?

320
00:24:21.664 --> 00:24:22.832
Nah. why would I?

321
00:24:23.057 --> 00:24:25.526
I'm familiar with architecture.

322
00:24:25.990 --> 00:24:28.075
Engineers use the term architecture...

323
00:24:28.164 --> 00:24:29.874
...for software structure too.

324
00:24:35.721 --> 00:24:36.737
Thank you.

325
00:24:36.799 --> 00:24:37.537
Applause!

326
00:24:40.735 --> 00:24:41.611
Wait.

327
00:24:41.912 --> 00:24:42.739
Gameboy?

328
00:24:43.129 --> 00:24:43.921
The gamer?

329
00:24:44.024 --> 00:24:44.748
Yes.

330
00:24:44.844 --> 00:24:46.049
I've heard much about you.

331
00:24:46.138 --> 00:24:47.042
Everyone!

332
00:24:47.181 --> 00:24:50.916
Who got into Gaudi. one of the top 3
architectural firms?

333
00:24:50.999 --> 00:24:52.512
The hero of our club Seum!

334
00:24:52.761 --> 00:24:55.292
Let's hear from Kang Min-jae.
a future star architect!

335
00:24:55.332 --> 00:24:56.683
Applause!

336
00:24:59.385 --> 00:25:00.507
Thank you!

337
00:25:00.838 --> 00:25:02.246
Thanks everyone.

338
00:25:02.493 --> 00:25:03.518
Today.

339
00:25:04.484 --> 00:25:06.846
it's on me. Eat all you want.

340
00:25:06.913 --> 00:25:09.166
Let's all toast to Seum.

341
00:25:09.307 --> 00:25:10.058
Let's go!

342
00:25:10.291 --> 00:25:11.279
Let's soar!

343
00:25:11.557 --> 00:25:13.893
Seum!

344
00:25:15.798 --> 00:25:17.981
Keep an eye on Yoon-jin.

345
00:25:19.121 --> 00:25:19.913
Jeong-won.

346
00:25:21.964 --> 00:25:25.328
I saw your designs last time.

347
00:25:25.600 --> 00:25:27.664
You're not an architecture major.

348
00:25:27.854 --> 00:25:29.381
but you got talent.

349
00:25:29.896 --> 00:25:31.857
I do?

350
00:25:32.753 --> 00:25:33.469
Yes.

351
00:25:34.157 --> 00:25:36.250
I was really surprised.

352
00:25:37.844 --> 00:25:40.907
If you had majored in it.
you would've been outstanding.

353
00:25:41.137 --> 00:25:42.806
Really?

354
00:25:44.132 --> 00:25:46.468
So. can I give you more tips?

355
00:25:47.074 --> 00:25:49.896
I'd love that. but you're busy.

356
00:25:50.005 --> 00:25:52.787
Of course.
I can make time for you.

357
00:25:54.555 --> 00:25:56.013
Thank you.

358
00:25:56.563 --> 00:25:58.384
- No need to thank me.
- Hey.

359
00:25:59.010 --> 00:26:00.074
Are you crazy?

360
00:26:00.567 --> 00:26:02.069
Don't eat the shell.

361
00:26:02.542 --> 00:26:03.258
What?

362
00:26:05.913 --> 00:26:07.366
We eat like this in my hometown.

363
00:26:26.191 --> 00:26:27.752
Do you want to go out with me?

364
00:26:29.459 --> 00:26:30.407
What?

365
00:26:31.169 --> 00:26:32.580
I swear...

366
00:26:33.922 --> 00:26:35.465
...I'll be good to you.

367
00:26:36.084 --> 00:26:37.168
Jerk.

368
00:26:37.759 --> 00:26:38.816
Jeong-won!

369
00:26:39.135 --> 00:26:40.428
Got a smoke?

370
00:26:40.880 --> 00:26:41.916
No. Damn it!

371
00:26:41.999 --> 00:26:43.382
Do you smoke?

372
00:26:43.966 --> 00:26:45.286
Where do you live?

373
00:26:45.433 --> 00:26:48.870
Tell us where you live.

374
00:26:48.910 --> 00:26:50.632
- Tower...
- What?

375
00:26:50.682 --> 00:26:51.808
Tower Pal...

376
00:26:52.865 --> 00:26:54.164
Where are you going?

377
00:26:54.402 --> 00:26:55.486
NEIGHBORHOOD PATROL

378
00:26:55.604 --> 00:26:56.856
Let's leave him here.

379
00:26:57.246 --> 00:26:58.496
They'll take him home.

380
00:26:59.032 --> 00:27:00.367
No!

381
00:27:01.047 --> 00:27:02.174
Oops. Sorry.

382
00:27:02.236 --> 00:27:03.196
Stop it!

383
00:27:04.398 --> 00:27:06.275
Come inside.

384
00:27:10.842 --> 00:27:11.718
Damn!

385
00:27:15.170 --> 00:27:18.393
<i>Lend me the money. prick!</i>

386
00:27:20.085 --> 00:27:21.475
<i>What the hell!
I'm on the phone here!</i>

387
00:27:22.098 --> 00:27:23.102
Don't mind that.

388
00:27:24.767 --> 00:27:26.894
If it gets worse. call me.

389
00:27:26.978 --> 00:27:27.895
Then what?

390
00:27:28.000 --> 00:27:29.192
Just come to my place.

391
00:27:29.414 --> 00:27:30.637
The key is under the tree pot.

392
00:27:31.315 --> 00:27:32.232
Get going. then.

393
00:27:32.879 --> 00:27:33.779
Right.

394
00:27:34.326 --> 00:27:37.088
Let me rest first. I'm exhausted.

395
00:27:37.739 --> 00:27:39.195
I'll stay for a bit.

396
00:27:39.567 --> 00:27:40.638
I'm beat.

397
00:27:44.016 --> 00:27:45.524
You like this architecture boy?

398
00:27:46.431 --> 00:27:47.672
No.

399
00:27:47.930 --> 00:27:48.799
I just...

400
00:27:50.738 --> 00:27:52.240
...think being an architect is cool.

401
00:27:52.914 --> 00:27:55.507
It's amazing
how they build homes by hand.

402
00:27:56.572 --> 00:27:58.700
He's a newbie. not an architect.

403
00:27:58.726 --> 00:27:59.713
He'll probably...

404
00:27:59.992 --> 00:28:01.333
...just be carrying planks.

405
00:28:01.827 --> 00:28:03.412
But if you dive into architecture.

406
00:28:04.593 --> 00:28:06.234
I know you'll make it
as an architect.

407
00:28:07.318 --> 00:28:08.806
Not everyone can do that.

408
00:28:09.410 --> 00:28:11.322
You need a degree in architecture.

409
00:28:11.776 --> 00:28:13.575
and at least 5 years
of work experience...

410
00:28:13.601 --> 00:28:15.478
...at a firm to qualify for the exam.

411
00:28:15.952 --> 00:28:17.163
Is it that tough?

412
00:28:25.722 --> 00:28:27.230
He said he'd be good to me.

413
00:28:27.416 --> 00:28:28.634
Even give you his heart?

414
00:28:30.745 --> 00:28:32.538
Why would I need his heart?

415
00:28:32.625 --> 00:28:34.126
It's not like
I have a heart condition.

416
00:28:34.208 --> 00:28:36.295
It's a metaphor.

417
00:28:36.953 --> 00:28:39.039
- You're poetic?
- Of course.

418
00:28:41.848 --> 00:28:43.123
So. are you going to date him?

419
00:28:48.021 --> 00:28:49.106
Not sure.

420
00:28:50.866 --> 00:28:53.343
If I had a girlfriend.

421
00:28:53.388 --> 00:28:54.928
I'm going to treat her
like a queen.

422
00:28:56.119 --> 00:28:57.058
But you don't.

423
00:28:57.531 --> 00:28:58.657
I can dream. can't I?

424
00:29:04.156 --> 00:29:05.199
You should go.

425
00:29:26.415 --> 00:29:27.360
Hi!

426
00:29:34.550 --> 00:29:36.927
Sorry! I was stuck in traffic.

427
00:29:37.253 --> 00:29:38.506
I'll go and change.

428
00:29:38.532 --> 00:29:40.479
Sure! Go ahead.

429
00:29:43.246 --> 00:29:45.759
GAME CLUB. BULLIZZARD

430
00:29:50.921 --> 00:29:53.899
SEA...

431
00:29:57.434 --> 00:29:58.185
<i>The sea?</i>

432
00:29:58.303 --> 00:30:00.833
Jeong-won wanted to get some air.

433
00:30:01.180 --> 00:30:03.989
I can show her the cafe
that I designed. too.

434
00:30:07.222 --> 00:30:08.084
Spending the night?

435
00:30:09.238 --> 00:30:09.877
What?

436
00:30:10.077 --> 00:30:10.849
Nothing.

437
00:30:13.249 --> 00:30:14.626
- Ready?
- Let's go.

438
00:30:14.866 --> 00:30:17.110
- Come on.
- Thanks. You just need to cover until 12.

439
00:30:17.339 --> 00:30:18.154
See you.

440
00:30:19.621 --> 00:30:20.976
- Min-jae. hold on.
- Yes.

441
00:30:21.017 --> 00:30:22.061
Hey!

442
00:30:22.221 --> 00:30:23.479
Do I look pretty?

443
00:30:23.690 --> 00:30:24.983
Not bad.

444
00:30:27.000 --> 00:30:27.678
See you!

445
00:30:40.622 --> 00:30:45.383
- You go in first.
- No. you go ahead.

446
00:30:49.100 --> 00:30:50.555
Come and sit for a meeting.

447
00:30:50.953 --> 00:30:53.191
We got 2 weeks till the contest.

448
00:30:53.792 --> 00:30:56.329
- You say it.
- No. you say it.

449
00:31:00.556 --> 00:31:01.480
What is it?

450
00:31:02.189 --> 00:31:02.940
Eun-ho.

451
00:31:03.774 --> 00:31:06.062
- I've been thinking.
- Right.

452
00:31:06.849 --> 00:31:09.512
The contest is important.

453
00:31:09.637 --> 00:31:10.715
We know...

454
00:31:10.824 --> 00:31:12.672
We should also think about
what happens if we fail.

455
00:31:12.698 --> 00:31:13.453
So?

456
00:31:14.997 --> 00:31:18.083
We thought it'd be more realistic...

457
00:31:18.129 --> 00:31:20.381
...to manage our grades from now on.

458
00:31:21.128 --> 00:31:23.540
Hey. that's your excuse
for betraying me?

459
00:31:23.566 --> 00:31:25.141
What?

460
00:31:25.238 --> 00:31:26.162
Betray?

461
00:31:26.634 --> 00:31:27.426
You too?

462
00:31:27.518 --> 00:31:29.569
At first. I thought he was crazy.

463
00:31:29.746 --> 00:31:32.329
but it's actually quite logical.

464
00:31:32.374 --> 00:31:33.524
Right.

465
00:31:36.073 --> 00:31:38.642
You can't make $10 million
on a salary. guys.

466
00:31:39.300 --> 00:31:41.074
What about dealing stocks
with your pay?

467
00:31:41.287 --> 00:31:44.231
- Not a bad idea.
- Right?

468
00:31:50.150 --> 00:31:51.016
Jeong-won!

469
00:31:53.341 --> 00:31:56.177
Jeez!

470
00:31:57.012 --> 00:31:58.008
I can't breathe.

471
00:31:59.405 --> 00:32:01.323
Did you drink?
Why is your face so red?

472
00:32:01.613 --> 00:32:03.952
Kyung-seok and Seung-chan...

473
00:32:05.375 --> 00:32:06.709
Just forget it.

474
00:32:09.817 --> 00:32:12.278
My place is a bit messy.

475
00:32:23.817 --> 00:32:24.870
Hold on.

476
00:32:34.050 --> 00:32:34.885
Do you want some water?

477
00:32:34.982 --> 00:32:36.400
- No. it's okay.
- Okay.

478
00:32:38.186 --> 00:32:39.469
Can I put this here?

479
00:32:39.717 --> 00:32:40.717
Sure.

480
00:33:04.139 --> 00:33:05.329
Why aren't you asking?

481
00:33:06.000 --> 00:33:06.817
What?

482
00:33:07.001 --> 00:33:08.076
Why we broke up.

483
00:33:08.816 --> 00:33:12.121
I'm sure you had your reasons.

484
00:33:17.255 --> 00:33:18.802
I met his mom.

485
00:33:20.321 --> 00:33:21.409
She lives by the sea?

486
00:33:23.435 --> 00:33:24.885
We met by chance.

487
00:33:25.912 --> 00:33:27.914
She asked about my background.

488
00:33:28.068 --> 00:33:31.236
I told her honestly that I'm an orphan
and I live in a tiny dorm.

489
00:33:31.492 --> 00:33:34.303
Then her face turned red
and she started crying.

490
00:33:35.089 --> 00:33:36.167
She pitied me.

491
00:33:36.760 --> 00:33:37.946
What the hell?

492
00:33:38.889 --> 00:33:41.387
Then she went on and on
about stuff.

493
00:33:42.208 --> 00:33:43.667
The gist of it was that...

494
00:33:44.926 --> 00:33:46.301
...I don't need to be rich.

495
00:33:46.327 --> 00:33:49.414
but a good upbringing matters.

496
00:33:50.381 --> 00:33:52.787
Well. I think that too.

497
00:33:53.835 --> 00:33:55.332
But what can I do?

498
00:33:56.359 --> 00:33:58.809
Min-jae just sat there
with his mouth shut.

499
00:34:01.121 --> 00:34:03.107
Back in my room.

500
00:34:04.576 --> 00:34:06.359
through the tiny window.

501
00:34:08.406 --> 00:34:10.328
<i>sunlight was coming in.
just the size of my palm.</i>

502
00:34:14.510 --> 00:34:17.294
<i>Even sunlight...
I can only get this much.</i>

503
00:34:18.431 --> 00:34:20.041
<i>Just a handful.</i>

504
00:34:22.456 --> 00:34:24.792
<i>Damn jerks!</i>

505
00:34:26.161 --> 00:34:28.330
<i>How dare you!</i>

506
00:34:29.018 --> 00:34:30.523
So. I got sad.

507
00:34:32.835 --> 00:34:33.836
That's it.

508
00:35:00.259 --> 00:35:01.341
You can have it.

509
00:35:09.942 --> 00:35:12.303
I'll stay here until I find a place.

510
00:35:13.130 --> 00:35:16.092
I'll pay half the rent.
Don't you dare try to rip me off.

511
00:35:16.224 --> 00:35:16.899
Okay.

512
00:35:16.961 --> 00:35:19.373
I'll pay half the utilities and...

513
00:35:19.953 --> 00:35:20.965
Jeong-won.

514
00:35:23.158 --> 00:35:24.705
I'm glad you came.

515
00:35:37.750 --> 00:35:38.629
Coming.

516
00:35:44.383 --> 00:35:45.592
What brings you here?

517
00:35:45.662 --> 00:35:47.414
Hi. Eun-ho. You were home.

518
00:35:47.500 --> 00:35:48.171
Yes.

519
00:35:48.317 --> 00:35:50.461
My laptop is wacked again.

520
00:35:53.573 --> 00:35:54.319
Girlfriend?

521
00:35:54.788 --> 00:35:56.082
We're bosom buddies.

522
00:35:57.016 --> 00:35:58.497
Bosom buddies?

523
00:35:59.174 --> 00:36:00.467
Bosom?

524
00:36:01.351 --> 00:36:03.353
It crashed and froze.

525
00:36:04.684 --> 00:36:05.873
It did?

526
00:36:06.539 --> 00:36:07.208
Yeah.

527
00:36:07.489 --> 00:36:09.992
You can just reinstall Windows.
Want me to do it?

528
00:36:10.424 --> 00:36:11.817
Yes. do it.

529
00:36:13.399 --> 00:36:14.222
Okay.

530
00:36:15.382 --> 00:36:16.627
Need to backup anything?

531
00:36:16.947 --> 00:36:18.295
No. just do it.

532
00:36:18.411 --> 00:36:21.138
Okay. then.

533
00:36:21.289 --> 00:36:23.308
- Wait. please.
- Sure.

534
00:36:28.706 --> 00:36:29.870
Sorry.

535
00:36:31.633 --> 00:36:32.627
<i>Baby!</i>

536
00:36:32.760 --> 00:36:34.038
Coming.

537
00:36:34.386 --> 00:36:35.221
Eun-ho.

538
00:36:35.346 --> 00:36:36.270
Just do it for me.

539
00:36:36.346 --> 00:36:37.847
I'll back up everything.

540
00:36:37.953 --> 00:36:38.870
Thanks. See ya!

541
00:36:41.518 --> 00:36:45.015
"Eun-ho. just do it for me."

542
00:36:45.872 --> 00:36:47.382
Gross.

543
00:36:47.803 --> 00:36:48.929
Why? She's cute.

544
00:36:50.098 --> 00:36:50.831
Cute?

545
00:36:51.095 --> 00:36:52.103
That's cute?

546
00:36:52.238 --> 00:36:53.855
Want me to point out details?

547
00:36:55.408 --> 00:36:57.184
Those aren't prescription glasses?

548
00:36:57.864 --> 00:37:00.376
Maybe you should wear glasses
to help with your taste in men.

549
00:37:03.417 --> 00:37:04.543
- Why you!
- Ow!

550
00:37:14.101 --> 00:37:15.258
You can take the bed.

551
00:37:16.173 --> 00:37:17.341
No. you can.

552
00:37:17.772 --> 00:37:19.857
I'm fine here. You take it.

553
00:37:20.275 --> 00:37:22.387
But it's your bed.

554
00:37:22.610 --> 00:37:23.361
Sleep on the bed.

555
00:37:31.314 --> 00:37:32.315
Thanks.

556
00:37:36.937 --> 00:37:37.907
Lights out.

557
00:37:38.376 --> 00:37:39.270
Okay.

558
00:37:54.873 --> 00:37:56.176
Dang.

559
